Panettone // Season 11 @hofkelsten 

Hof Kelsten Panettone’s are individually crafted by hand, adhering time-honored Italian traditions. Each of these panettones is a product of a meticulous 72-hour process, free from additives, artificial colors, or commercial yeast. Instead, they boast a distinctive natural yeast, dating back to the 1970s. This yeast journeyed from Italy to Spain, where the panettone’s method was perfected, before finally arriving at Hof Kelsten.

The Chocolate Panettone features 64% Premier Cru Valrhona Mangari chocolate, along with orange confit and lemon, whereas the Classic variant contains raisins, orange confit, lemon, and almonds.

Get one while you can. If not, there’s always next year.
